German Car-Delivery Times Causing Concern, Automobilwoche Says

-- B y   O l i v e r   S u e s s
-- 
2011-05-28T10:42:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-28/german-car-delivery-times-causing-concern-automobilwoche-says.html
German carmakers including  Daimler
AG (DAI) ,  Bayerische Motoren Werke AG (BMW)  and  Volkswagen AG (VOW)  are concerned
at the length of delivery times on customer orders,
Automobilwoche reported, citing industry executives.  Buyers have to wait as long as 10 months for their cars and
Nick Margetts, a manager at Jato Dynamics consulting company,
said the situation is unlikely to get better before 2012, the
magazine said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Oliver Suess in Munich at 
 osuess@bloomberg.net   To contact the editors responsible for this story:
Frank Connelly at   fconnelly@bloomberg.net 
Edward Evans at   eevans3@bloomberg.net  